00:41:52,719 --> 00:42:02,719
But Maud and what's his name? His grandfather, Tossi, Applement.

239
00:42:02,719 --> 00:42:11,719
Porter. Porter, Inkler, Applement. They were a real presence in his life.

240
00:42:11,719 --> 00:42:23,719
And Paul makes, I think, more of a psychological play on the boy who grew up without a father or something.

241
00:42:23,719 --> 00:42:34,719
Porter was a pretty pronounced presence in his life. And my association with Bill, his grandparents were very important.

242
00:42:34,719 --> 00:42:42,719
And he was very proud of his mother, of course.

243
00:42:42,719 --> 00:42:53,719
I have one other thing I want to say about his upbringing in Atlantic. And he makes mention of 1927.

